Walter Bruce Willis -LRB- born March 19 , 1955 -RRB- is an American actor , producer , and singer .
His career began on the Off-Broadway stage and then in television in the 1980s , most notably as David Addison in Moonlighting -LRB- 1985 -- 1989 -RRB- .
He is known for his role of John McClane in the Die Hard series .
He has appeared in over 60 films , including Color of Night -LRB- 1994 -RRB- , Pulp Fiction -LRB- 1994 -RRB- , 12 Monkeys -LRB- 1995 -RRB- , The Fifth Element -LRB- 1997 -RRB- , Armageddon -LRB- 1998 -RRB- , The Sixth Sense -LRB- 1999 -RRB- , Unbreakable -LRB- 2000 -RRB- , Sin City -LRB- 2005 -RRB- , Red -LRB- 2010 -RRB- , The Expendables 2 -LRB- 2012 -RRB- , and Looper -LRB- 2012 -RRB- .
Willis married actress Demi Moore in 1987 , and they had three daughters , including Rumer , before their divorce in 2000 .
Since 2009 , he has been married to model Emma Heming , with whom he has two daughters .